The paper deals with a machine learning problem of class-imbalance in multi-label datasets. The proposed method is a resampling technique that generates synthetic instances based on local label distribution. This problem and solution are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on machine learning and classification, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV. The other two sub-categories are also relevant but less likely to be the primary category.
